<bibRefCitation id="EF9F76D8C921FFD0FF13C76DFE603028" author="Hunt, G. S. &amp; Colloff, M. J. &amp; Dallwitz, M. &amp; Walter, D. E." box="[215,384,1882,1907]" pageId="12" pageNumber="302" refId="ref20301" refString="Hunt, G. S., Colloff, M. J., Dallwitz, M. &amp; Walter, D. E. (1998) An Interactive Key to Oribatid Mites of Australia. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne. [CD-ROM]" type="book" year="1998">
Hunt 
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC921FFD0FED4C76DFEA43029" box="[272,324,1882,1906]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="302">et al.</emphasis>
1998
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB10B29C920FFD1FF03C0AFFB123644" blockId="13.[151,1437,153,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF03C0AFFE8B37E8" box="[199,363,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Lateral aspect</emphasis>
: apices of lamellar cusps slightly curved ventrally. Interlamellar region slightly domed, level with highest part of centrodorsal ridge. Anterior margin of rostrum between tutorium (
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FBA3C088FB9D378C" box="[1127,1149,190,215]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">tu</emphasis>
) and rostral seta straight, diagonal. Tutorium with short free cusp. Anterior margin of pedotectum I rounded, convex. Centrodorsal ridge low and flat, extending posteriorly as far as level of lyrifissure 
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FCE3C133FCDD3644" box="[807,829,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">ih</emphasis>
; region just posterior slightly concave.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB10B29C920FFD1FF03C11CFF1F36F4" blockId="13.[151,1437,153,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF03C11CFF1C3618" box="[199,252,298,323]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Legs</emphasis>
: Tarsus I with 15 setae, including short setiform famulus; solenidia ω 
<subScript id="178A096CC920FFD1FBC2C10CFBEE3613" attach="left" box="[1030,1038,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">1</subScript>
and ω 
<subScript id="178A096CC920FFD1FB92C10CFBBE3613" attach="left" box="[1110,1118,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">2</subScript>
subequal in length (
<quantity id="4CF6A6CCC920FFD1FA85C11FFA6F3618" box="[1345,1423,297,323]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" unit="mm" value="30.0">30 µm</quantity>
); tibia I with solenidion φ 
<subScript id="178A096CC920FFD1FE61C168FE4D3637" attach="left" box="[421,429,350,364]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">1</subScript>
very long (
<quantity id="4CF6A6CCC920FFD1FDEAC17BFD69363C" box="[558,649,333,359]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" unit="mm" value="110.0">110 µm</quantity>
), flagelliform, arising free on tarsal cuticle and set back from articulation with tibia. Genu I without setae, bearing short solenidion σ only; femur I with one dorsal and one ventral seta (
<figureCitation id="133517ACC920FFD1FF64C1A3FF1136F4" box="[160,241,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1002,1027]" captionTargetBox="[242,1353,191,965]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[227,1361,181,977]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Topalia royi sp. nov. (a) left leg I; (b) chelicera; scale bars: (a) = 100 µm; (b) = 25 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3353120/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Fig. 8a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
