<paragraph id="8BB10B29C920FFD1FF03C213FD0635DC" blockId="13.[151,1437,153,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF03C213FEA83564" bold="true" box="[199,328,549,575]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named in honour and memory of Dr Alexander “Sandy” Bilton Roy in recognition of his nearly twenty years of volunteer work devoted to the curation and cataloguing of spiders, mites, ticks and termites in the Australian National Insect Collection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB10B29C920FFD1FF03C2A6FF123460" blockId="13.[151,1437,153,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF03C2A6FEA235F0" bold="true" box="[199,322,656,683]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FE83C2A7FE2D35F0" authority="Colloff, 2019" authorityName="Colloff" authorityYear="2019" box="[327,461,657,683]" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FE83C2A7FE2D35F0" box="[327,461,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Topalia royi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2496A40C920FFD1FE17C2A7FDCC35F0" box="[467,556,657,683]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FE17C2A7FDCC35F0" bold="true" box="[467,556,657,683]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished from other species in the genus by the following combination of characters: (1) the rostrum incised medially; (2) the anteromedial edges of lamellae separated; (3) the partly fused epimera 
<collectionCode id="ED1F93ECC920FFD1FEFFC2EFFEB735A8" box="[315,343,729,755]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">III</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="ED1F93ECC920FFD1FE48C2EFFE4B35A8" box="[396,427,729,755]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">IV</collectionCode>
; (4) the medially indented anterior notogastral margin; (4) the laterally-positioned humeral projections; (5) the cerotegument consisting of a network of large, deep, angular foveolae; (6) the epimeral setation 2-1-2-3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB10B29C920FFD1FF03C373FF0234D8" blockId="13.[151,1437,153,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF03C373FED43404" bold="true" box="[199,308,837,863]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FE81C373FE303404" authority="Colloff, 2019" authorityName="Colloff" authorityYear="2019" box="[325,464,837,863]" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FE81C373FE303404" box="[325,464,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Topalia royi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2496A40C920FFD1FE1EC373FDD63404" box="[474,566,837,863]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FE1EC373FDD63404" bold="true" box="[474,566,837,863]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FC1CC373FB4B3404" authority="Colloff, 2019" authorityName="Colloff" authorityYear="2019" box="[984,1195,837,863]" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caliginosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FC1CC373FB4B3404" box="[984,1195,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Topalia caliginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2496A40C920FFD1FB71C373FAF13404" box="[1205,1297,837,863]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FB71C373FAF13404" bold="true" box="[1205,1297,837,863]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, as detailed above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB10B29C920FFD1FF03C3BBFC163300" blockId="13.[151,1437,153,1115]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FF03C3BBFEFC34FC" authorityName="Balogh &amp; Csiszar" authorityYear="1963" box="[199,284,909,935]" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF03C3BBFEFC34FC" box="[199,284,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Topalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 2 (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F76D8C920FFD1FEA2C3BBFDC534FC" author="Hunt, G. S. &amp; Colloff, M. J. &amp; Dallwitz, M. &amp; Walter, D. E." box="[358,549,909,935]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" refId="ref20301" refString="Hunt, G. S., Colloff, M. J., Dallwitz, M. &amp; Walter, D. E. (1998) An Interactive Key to Oribatid Mites of Australia. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne. [CD-ROM]" type="book" year="1998">
Hunt 
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FE62C3B8FE3734FC" box="[422,471,909,935]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">et al</emphasis>
., 1998
</bibRefCitation>
) was collected from the same location as 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FC3CC3B8FBA034FC" authorityName="Colloff" authorityYear="2019" box="[1016,1088,910,935]" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royi">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FC3CC3B8FBA034FC" box="[1016,1088,910,935]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">T. royi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(leaf litter, O’Reilly’s Rainforest Retreat, Lamington National Park, 
<collectingRegion id="49CAC5CBC920FFD1FD8FC387FD2F3490" box="[587,719,945,971]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<geoCoordinate id="EE3A6DEEC920FFD1FD1BC387FCD93490" box="[735,825,945,971]" degrees="28" direction="south" minutes="14" orientation="latitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" precision="925" value="-28.233334">28º14’S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="EE3A6DEEC920FFD1FC85C386FC4B3490" box="[833,939,944,971]" degrees="153" direction="east" minutes="08" orientation="longitude" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" precision="925" value="153.13333">153º08’E</geoCoordinate>
) coll. R. Kitching) and I consider it to be 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FA4CC384FF2334B4" authority="Colloff, 2019" authorityName="Colloff" authorityYear="2019" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FA4CC384FF2334B4" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">T. royi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2496A40C920FFD1FF0FC3E3FEC834B4" box="[203,296,981,1007]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF0FC3E3FEC134B4" bold="true" box="[203,289,981,1007]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
They share the characteristic pattern of cerotegument, faint striae on the lamellar cusps, equal ratios of prodorsal length to total length, notogastral length to breadth, and the morphology of the bothridial setae (
<figureCitation id="133517ACC920FFD1FAABC3CFFF563363" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1846,1871]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,1049,1821]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[227,1361,1049,1821]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 9. Scanning electron micrographs of dorsal aspects of (a) Topalia sp. 1 and (b) Topalia royi sp. nov. (Topalia sp. 2) (from Hunt et al. 1998)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3353122/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Fig. 9b</figureCitation>
). When the figure of the dorsal aspect of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FD46C428FD29336C" authority="Colloff, 2019" authorityName="Colloff" authorityYear="2019" box="[642,713,1054,1079]" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="royi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FD46C428FD29336C" box="[642,713,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">T. royi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2496A40C920FFD1FD0BC42BFCC6336C" box="[719,806,1053,1079]" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is superimposed on the scanning electron micrograph of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E70AAC920FFD1FF53C477FF0C3300" authorityName="Balogh &amp; Csiszar" authorityYear="1963" box="[151,236,1089,1115]" class="Arachnida" family="Nosybeidae" genus="Topalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sarcoptiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="303" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AD73BC920FFD1FF53C477FF0C3300" box="[151,236,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="303">Topalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. 2, it fits almost exactly the outline of the lamellae and notogaster.
</paragraph>
